{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require farmers to fence off cattle from public footpaths for safety",
        "additional_details": "We think cattle-related incidents on public paths pose significant risks to walkers and pets, with fatalities and injuries continuing to occur in recent years. While respecting farmers\u2019 rights and land use needs, we think separating livestock from public paths is vital for safety. We believe mandatory fencing or barriers would protect the public, support responsible livestock management, and ensure safe countryside access.",
        "background": "We urge the UK Government to require farmers to use fencing, barriers, or safe diversions to separate cattle from public paths, especially in high-traffic areas. We think this would ensure public safety while respecting farming practices and promoting awareness about responsible cattle management.",
